jsumitro:
@Z008 : Yes. My finding is similar with yours. It is because the BACKUP_PLAYING_BUFFERING_STATE is storing a wrong state. In other device, the BACKUP_PLAYING_BUFFERING_STATE is set to CURRENT_STATE_PLAYING. However, in S8, it somehow set to CURRENT_STATE_PREPARING. Hence, the video is stuck at the spinning loading indicator while the sound is still playing.
@lipangit : I fix it by setting the current state to CURRENT_STATE_PLAYING directly after the buffering is finished. I am not sure whether it is a correct way or not but it solved my problem.

