achalkias:
What is the difference between your recyclerview and demo's recyclerview?

Hi, I have an activity that has a fragment pager and inside the first fragment i have a recyclerview with the posts. Now in the recyclerview. In the recyclerview adapter layout i have a JzvdStd player. It does not crash when the setUp is happening. But it crash when i click the play button.
I suspect it cannot find the activity because i use it from a fragment in a fragment pager?. > do you mean getAppCompActivity() the function can not get real Activity's context
Yes it crashes on this line 
return getAppCompActivity(((ContextThemeWrapper) context).getBaseContext());. > getAppCompActivity() this function did not fond in that log, how can sure it because it.
Ok my mistake i copied the wrong function. Sorry. This issue really got me.
The problem is here 
```
 public static Activity scanForActivity(Context context) {
        if (context == null) return null;
    if (context instanceof Activity) {
        return (Activity) context;
    } else if (context instanceof ContextWrapper) {
        return scanForActivity(((ContextWrapper) context).getBaseContext());
    }

    return null;
}

```
It runs it one time it goes to 
return scanForActivity(((ContextWrapper) context).getBaseContext());
Then it calls it self and the next time it just returns null in the end 
So the final crash happens here in line 601 of Jzvd.class
JZUtils.scanForActivity(getContext()).getWindow().addFlags(WindowManager.LayoutParams.FLAG_KEEP_SCREEN_ON);
Because the scanForActivity returns null and this is why it cannot find the window. I dont understand why. 
The weird thing is that it works outside the recyclerview. In a simple view in the same fragment. Progress figured out what the issue was. So i as inflating the layout in the adapter like this 
val view = LayoutInflater.from(App.appContext).inflate(R.layout.layout_post, parent, false)
return ViewHolder(view)
Getting the context the application context as context to inflate the layout. So that was the issue because the context basically was not the activity context but the application context. This is why it could not convert it to activity and find the window.
So after i changed it to this code
val view = LayoutInflater.from(context).inflate(R.layout.layout_post, parent, false)
return ViewHolder(view)
Passing the activity context in the adapter. And now it works just fine.
So i close this. Hope this will help someone else. Thank you.
